Title: An Anatomy of Commodity Futures Risk Premia 
Author-Name: MARTA SZYMANOWSKA  
Author-Name: FRANS ROON  
Author-Name: THEO NIJMAN  
Author-Name: ROB GOORBERGH  
Abstract:
  type="main"> <title type="main">ABSTRACT</title> <p>We identify two types
 of risk premia in commodity futures returns: spot premia related to the
 risk in the underlying commodity, and term premia related to changes in
 the basis. Sorting on forecasting variables such as the futures basis,
 return momentum, volatility, inflation, hedging pressure, and liquidity
 results in sizable spot premia between 5% and 14% per annum and term
 premia between 1% and 3% per annum. We show that a single factor, the
 high-minus-low portfolio from basis sorts, explains the cross-section of
 spot premia. Two additional basis factors are needed to explain the term
 premia.
