Title: Who Writes the News? Corporate Press Releases during Merger Negotiations 
Author-Name: KENNETH R. AHERN  
Author-Name: DENIS SOSYURA  
Abstract:
  type="main"> <title type="main">ABSTRACT</title> <p>Firms have an
 incentive to manage media coverage to influence their stock prices during
 important corporate events. Using comprehensive data on media coverage and
 merger negotiations, we find that bidders in stock mergers originate
 substantially more news stories after the start of merger negotiations,
 but before the public announcement. This strategy generates a short-lived
 run-up in bidders' stock prices during the period when the stock exchange
 ratio is determined, which substantially impacts the takeover price. Our
 results demonstrate that the timing and content of financial media
 coverage may be biased by firms seeking to manipulate their stock price.
